## Follow-up: google_adk added
Reviewer asked if the Google ADK integration was missing from the OTel slice — it
was. google_adk is the third agent-OTel integration: it doesn't create spans of
its own; it patches ADK's trace_* tracing functions (trace_agent_invocation,
trace_tool_call, _set_common_generate_content_attributes, trace_inference_result)
to enrich the OTel spans ADK emits (which ride the TracerProvider weave.init()
configures). Added _INTEGRATION_OTEL_ATTRS = library_integration("google_adk",
distribution_name="google-adk").as_otel_attributes() and a _set_integration_attrs
helper, called in each of the 4 wrappers alongside the existing
gen_ai.provider.name set — so invoke_agent / execute_tool / generate_content spans
all carry integration.* provenance. (My original pattern-grep missed it because it
uses neither weave.op/op_settings nor create_call — only span.set_attribute.)
ruff + ast clean; google-adk lib not installed locally so not runtime-tested.

## Test coverage added (follow-up: "same for the otel integrations")

Stamped 3 agent-OTel integrations; the original commit added NO tests and (per its
own Testing note) couldn't import the libs, so the otel tests were never run.
Added flattened-key asserts (integration.name / integration.version /
integration.meta.package_name -- OTel spans store dotted scalar keys):

- openai_agents (openai_agents_otel_test.py::test_openai_agents_quickstart_otel) and
  google_adk (test_google_adk.py::TestAdkRunnerE2E::test_emits_all_otel_attributes):
  ADD-only robust asserts -- collect finished spans, require >=1 carrying
  integration.name, assert name + meta.package_name (openai_agents -> openai-agents;
  google_adk -> google-adk).

- claude_agent_sdk (claude_agent_sdk_otel_test.py::test_simple_text_query_otel):
  *** ALSO A BUG FIX ***. The commit .update()'s _INTEGRATION_OTEL_ATTRS into the
  chat / tool / turn attr dicts, but this test asserts the FULL attribute dict with
  EXACT equality (assert get_attrs(agent_span) == {...} and the same for chat_span).
  Adding integration.* keys BREAKS both exact-equality assertions. The author never
  caught it (couldn't run claude_agent_sdk locally). Fix: a
  check_integration_and_strip() helper pops + asserts the 3 integration.* keys and
  returns the remainder, so the exact-shape assertions stay focused on GenAI semconv
  keys AND the provenance is now asserted. Only test_simple_text_query_otel used
  full-dict exact-equality on stamped spans; the other claude otel tests use
  individual-key checks and were unaffected.

